Certainly! Below is the LaTeX code to generate a table containing the information of Name, Age, and Gender for the individuals John, Maria, and Peter. The code includes all the necessary packages.

```latex
\documentclass{article}
\usepackage{array}
\usepackage{booktabs}

\begin{document}

\begin{table}[h]
    \centering
    \begin{tabular}{>{\bfseries}l c c}
        \toprule
        Name  & Age & Gender \\
        \midrule
        John  & 25  & Male   \\
        Maria & 30  & Female \\
        Peter & 22  & Male   \\
        \bottomrule
    \end{tabular}
    \caption{Information of individuals}
    \label{tab:individuals}
\end{table}

\end{document}
```

This code will produce a neatly formatted table using the `booktabs` package for improved aesthetics. The table contains bold headers for the columns: Name, Age, and Gender, and displays the corresponding information for John, Maria, and Peter. You can compile this code using a LaTeX editor to view the table.
